 "text": "\n\nFix: \n\n\u003cvuxml xmlns=\"http://www.vuxml.org/apps/vuxml-1\"\u003e\n   \u003cvuln vid=\"7858507d-b58d-45cf-87ca-179f1e5a4fa7\"\u003e\n     \u003ctopic\u003ephplist -- phpList admin/index.php Local File Include\u003c/topic\u003e\n     \u003caffects\u003e\n       \u003cpackage\u003e\n         \u003cname\u003ephplist\u003c/name\u003e\n         \u003crange\u003e\u003cle\u003e2.10.8\u003c/le\u003e\u003c/range\u003e\n       \u003c/package\u003e\n     \u003c/affects\u003e\n     \u003cdescription\u003e\n       \u003cbody xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\u003e\n         \u003cp\u003eSANS reports:\u003c/p\u003e\n         \u003cblockquote cite=\"http://www.securityfocus.com/archive/1/500057\"\u003e\n           \u003cp\u003eThe application is\nexposed to a local file include issue because it fails to properly\nsanitize user-supplied input to the _SERVERConfigFile of the\nadmin/index.php script. phpList version 2.10.8 is affected.\u003c/p\u003e\n         \u003c/blockquote\u003e\n       \u003c/body\u003e\n     \u003c/description\u003e\n     \u003creferences\u003e\n      \u003curl\u003ehttp://www.securityfocus.com/archive/1/500057\u003c/url\u003e\n     \u003c/references\u003e\n     \u003cdates\u003e\n       \u003cdiscovery\u003e2009-01-14\u003c/discovery\u003e\n       \u003centry\u003e2009-01-23\u003c/entry\u003e\n     \u003c/dates\u003e\n   \u003c/vuln\u003e"
